
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `groff` baraye tabdil kardane matn-haye sade (ke ba dastoor zaban-e mark-up neveshte shode-and) be format-haye motefavet mesle PDF, PostScript, ya hatta namayesh dar terminal estefade mishavad.  In dastoor bishter baraye dorost kardane safahat-e rahnamaye (man pages) UNIX/Linux estefade mishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `groff -T ps file.troff`  --> 📄 Tabdil file `file.troff` be PostScript.
    🔹 `groff -T pdf file.troff > file.pdf`  --> 🖨️ Tabdil file `file.troff` be PDF.
    🔹 `groff -man file.man` --> 👨‍💻 Format kardane file `file.man` be shekl safhe-ye rahnamaye UNIX.  `man` macro package ro estefade mikone.
    🔹 `groff -help` --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye kamel baraye dastoor `groff`.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ groff -T ps my_document.troff > my_document.ps

    🔹 In dastoor file `my_document.troff` ra be file PostScript tabdil mikonad va dar file `my_document.ps` zakhire mikonad.

    $ groff -T pdf my_document.troff | evince -

    🔹 In dastoor file `my_document.troff` ra be PDF tabdil mikonad va be program `evince` (ya har PDF viewer dige) miferestad ta namayesh dade shavad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ groff -man man_page.txt | less

    🔹 In dastoor file `man_page.txt` ra be shekl safhe rahnamaye UNIX format mikonad va natije ra be `less` miferestad ta namayesh dade shavad. In baraye didane pishnevis-e safhe rahnamatoon ghabl az install kardanesh khoobe.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `groff` command is used to format plain text files (often written with a markup language) into various output formats such as PDF, PostScript, or even for display in the terminal. It is frequently used for creating UNIX/Linux manual pages.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `groff -T ps file.troff`  --> 📄 Convert the file `file.troff` to PostScript.
    🔹 `groff -T pdf file.troff > file.pdf`  --> 🖨️ Convert the file `file.troff` to PDF.
    🔹 `groff -man file.man` --> 👨‍💻 Format the file `file.man` as a UNIX manual page, using the `man` macro package.
    🔹 `groff -help` --> ❓ Display the full help information for the `groff` command.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ groff -T ps my_document.troff > my_document.ps

    🔹 This command converts the `my_document.troff` file to a PostScript file and saves it to `my_document.ps`.

    $ groff -T pdf my_document.troff | evince -

    🔹 This command converts the `my_document.troff` file to PDF format and pipes the output to the `evince` program (or any other PDF viewer) to be displayed.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ groff -man man_page.txt | less

    🔹 This command formats the `man_page.txt` file as a UNIX manual page and pipes the output to `less` for viewing. This is useful for previewing a man page before installing it.
